==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rubricate
<hw>Ru"bri*cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To mark or
distinguished with red; to arrange as in a rubric; to establish in a
settled and unchangeable form.</def> <rj><au>Foxe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A system . . . according to which the thoughts of men were to be
classed and <qex>rubricated</qex> forever after.</q>
<rj><qau>Hare.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rubricist</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Rubrician</ent>⟦br⟧
